"crowd of shitsacks" i found really good as well. totally just a bunch of tangential gore transitioning into each other. there's some sort of underlying message about humanity somewhere there, but in the end it's all failure, death, and despair. ooooo mega edge. i like. the rest, eh, pretty standard. i did like how the first work started with color. i wanted to gag.

absolutely cannot fap to this at all, and at its core it really all is just a bunch of goreshit oneshots put together into one anthology. truly a season of hell. i expected it to be like erogros where there's (sort of?) one story or overarching theme, but this has a bunch of different artist's works and honestly the only common theme i can see is uh... goreshit... some sort of dystopian fantasy shockfest... i'd already seen "The Holes" somewhere else by itself before, so seeing it here along with the other works was a pleasant(?) surprise! mostly because it's familiar, lol. most of the other stories were pretty forgettable, save for "Rotten Bud" and "Crowd of Shitsacks". Rotten Bud took me for surprise. It was a total dystopia among dystopias (even though it was post-ww2?) and its concepts were frankly just so absurd. it was disgusting, and i couldn't look away. loved how it ended, can't explain it properly. it did itself really well. i would reread just for that one.

244327 - high tier konosuba doujin featuring the main cast. 

10003 - A doujin about a girl from a boy’s past granting him (erotic) powers, great plot and great artwork, highly recommend reading. 

169134 - If you haven’t read or heard of yupiel already you are missing out, this is the same artist that created nagatoro. 

185294 - a boy is stalked by a yandere and falls in love.  

139512 - zombie girl, be aware it’s still kind of gore.

Rooten Bud by Mitsuka Hattori, a masterpiece hidden in a piece of crap. "As a lotus flower is born in water, grows in water and rises out of water to stand above it unsoiled, so I, born in the world, raised in the world having overcome the world, live unsoiled by the world. To be born by a flower and not by the rotten bud of a woman, must be of divine nature." Commensurately the protagonist is wearing the divine letters of kamikaze the pinnacle of Yamato spirite. Furthermore the art and the setting appeal to the elderly times, before Japan become fully effected by western degeneracy. In the early times the birth of a human was a sacred events, blessed by the gods. Today it's only the product of sexual lust and biological process, born in the technocracy coldness of a hospitale. Truly a rotten bud.
